=========================
ROLE BASED ACCESS PROMPT:
You are working on a Spring Boot backend that is already fully implemented (entities, services, controllers).
Your task is NOT to modify controllers or business logic, but ONLY to update the security roles and seed data in a clean, minimal, and realistic way.

## Context

The system manages research labs with entities such as:

* Lab, Member, Equipe, Production, Publication
* A User entity for authentication with Roles
* A Member entity linked to User and representing domain roles in labs

## Important Constraints

* DO NOT modify existing controllers or endpoints
* DO NOT merge User.roles with Member.roleInLab
* Use User.roles ONLY for authorization
* Use Member.roleInLab ONLY for business meaning
* Keep the solution simple and production-ready (no over-engineering)

## Required Roles (only these 4)

* ROLE_SUPER_ADMIN
* ROLE_LAB_DIRECTOR
* ROLE_TEAM_LEADER
* ROLE_RESEARCHER

## Permissions Matrix

### ROLE_SUPER_ADMIN

* Full access to all endpoints:

  * Users: create, read, update, delete
  * Labs: create, read, update, delete
  * Equipes: create, read, update, delete
  * Members: create, read, update, delete
  * Productions: create, read, update, delete
  * Publications: create, read, update, delete

### ROLE_LAB_DIRECTOR

* Scope: ONLY his Lab
* Can:

  * READ all data
  * CREATE/UPDATE/DELETE:

    * Equipes
    * Members
    * Productions
    * Publications
* Cannot:

  * Manage users globally
  * Modify other labs

### ROLE_TEAM_LEADER

* Scope: ONLY his Equipe
* Can:

  * READ all data
  * CREATE/UPDATE:

    * Publications
    * Productions (if linked to team)
* Cannot:

  * Delete labs or equipes
  * Manage members outside his team

### ROLE_RESEARCHER

* Scope: ONLY his Lab
* Can:

  * READ all data
  * CREATE:

    * Publications
* Can:

  * UPDATE only his own publications
* Cannot:

  * Delete data
  * Manage structure (labs, equipes, members)

## Data Seeding Requirements

* Create default roles in database
* Create at least:

  * 1 SUPER_ADMIN user
  * 1 LAB_DIRECTOR linked to a Member with roleInLab = DIRECTEUR
  * 1 TEAM_LEADER linked to a Member responsible of an Equipe
  * 1 RESEARCHER linked to a Member

## Security Design Rules

* Use role-based authorization (Spring Security)
* Do NOT hardcode lab/team filtering in roles
* Data ownership (lab/equipe) must be enforced at service level (not role explosion)

## Expected Output

* Clean role seeding logic
* Clean user creation with assigned roles
* No unnecessary complexity
* Ready for JWT-based security
